            "id": "9e7b7dc2c66c4265b80d8",
            "questionText": "A uniform rod of length $!$L = 1\\,\\text{m}$!$ and mass $!$M = 2\\,\\text{kg}$!$ is initially at rest on a frictionless horizontal surface. A force of $!$F = 10\\,\\text{N}$!$ is applied perpendicularly to one end of the rod. Calculate the instantaneous angular displacement of the rod after $!$t = 2\\,\\text{s}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "1e746c93713142be9ec91",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by determining how to compute the torque produced by the applied force. Identify the correct formula that relates torque to force and the lever arm (the distance from the center of mass to the point of force application).",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "66c394e5-9b27-4235-9105-6b2e0ba0b2b0"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\tau = Fd$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\tau = \\frac{F}{d}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\tau = Fr$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "cd5221b99a274ea1ab5cc",
                    "stepText": "Great. Now, use the lever arm value, which for a uniform rod is its half-length ($!$L/2$!$), along with the applied force to compute the torque. Calculate the torque value.",
